Interface Springable

All Known Implementing Classes:
AppController, AppUI, BoundCanvas, CanvasContentPane, CanvasPane, CellController, Console, ConsoleController, ConsoleElementController, ConsolePage, Content, ContentController, ContentManager, ContentPane, ContentSwitchDemoPage, ContentSwitchDemoPageController, Controller, DialogController, DummyInstancesContent, DummyInstancesContentController, EntityDebugPage, EntityDebugPageController, ExamplePage, ExamplePageController, FallbackPage, FallbackPageController, FxWeaverInitializer, ImageButton, LogiCore, MandelbrotContent, MandelbrotContentController, MandelbrotPage, MandelbrotPageController, Overlay, OverlayHandler, SettingGroupController, SettingsController, Sidebar, SidebarNodeGroupController, SimpleSpringable, StrictSpringable, TestContent, TestContentController, TestSettingGroupController, UIBook, UIPage, UIPageController
public interface Springable

Guarantees that all implementing classes will have direct access to...

  1. The appropriate ConfigurableApplicationContext instance, ideally global scope if available.
  2. An FxWeaver instance.

Details

  1. By default, both weaver() and ctx() methods are permitted to return null.
  2. Annotating implemented methods as either Nullable or NotNull to reflect nullity is strongly recommended.

    • asSimple

      @NotNull default @NotNull SimpleSpringable asSimple()

      Constructs a new SimpleSpringable instance wrapping the contents of this Springable.

      Details

      1. By passing the value of this method wherever a Springable is required permits this Springable instance to be garbage collected when no longer used.
      2. This prevents the possibility of an unnecessary reference to this Springable instance from accidentally being stored as a Springable, preventing garbage collection.
      Returns:
      A new SimpleSpringable instance wrapping the contents of this Springable.

    • asStrict

      @NotNull default @NotNull StrictSpringable asStrict()

      Identical to asSimple(), except the Springable returned by this method is strict.

      Refer to asSimple() for additional information.
      Returns:
      A new StrictSpringable instance wrapping the contents of this Springable.
